* She watched him, very carefully as he began to move back, still slightly 
recognizing him but not to the point which she knew who he was.
The mode stopped and cocked her head to the side, the whip-like tail still 
thrashing behind her as she watched.
But with Prowls gun raised towards her, tensions were high.
The creature glared at him with her black eyes, long bony spiles along the 
spine of her back rising just a little, staring at the gun in Prowls hand.
She knew that gun, or thought she did. But the memory was so far away.

The mode started pacing a bit, back and fourth slowly in front of Prowl. Her 
head pointed towards him at all times.
But, suddenly this male bot spoke, and she recognized the name. He said, 
understood the word he spoke.
She stopped moving, suddenly stiff and alert, staring at him. Her head 
cocked to the side, as if asking him to repeat what he had just said.*
